# DimagX 🧠

**Project brain for coding agents.**  
One init. Drop your PRDs. Switch models freely — your agent always knows where you left off.

---

## What it does

DimagX builds a persistent memory graph for your project — code, features, prompts, PRDs, git history, and architectural decisions — and exposes it to any coding agent via MCP.

Instead of your agent re-reading 50 files every session, it calls `get_context()` and gets a precise, oriented summary in seconds.

---

## Install

```bash
pip install dimagx
```

Or from source:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourname/dimagx
cd dimagx
pip install -e .
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# Go to any project (new or existing)
cd my-project

# Initialize DimagX
dimagx init

# See what's in memory
dimagx status

# See where you left off
dimagx context
```

---

## Commands

### Project
```bash
dimagx init          # Scan project, build memory graph
dimagx status        # Memory dashboard — counts per layer
dimagx context       # Human-readable: features, commits, prompts, PRDs
dimagx watch         # Background watcher — auto re-index on file save
```

### Features
```bash
dimagx feature start "Pricing Engine"   # Tag active work
dimagx feature done  "Pricing Engine"   # Mark complete
dimagx feature list                      # Show all features + status
```

### PRDs
```bash
dimagx prd ingest ./docs/pricing.md     # Summarize + store PRD (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
dimagx prd list                          # List all PRDs
dimagx prd show "Pricing Engine"        # Full PRD details + linked features
```

### Decisions (ADRs)
```bash
dimagx decision add                     # Log architectural decision (interactive)
dimagx decision list                    # Show all decisions
```

### Git Hook
```bash
dimagx hook install                     # Auto-log every commit to graph
dimagx hook uninstall                   # Remove hook
```

### MCP Server (for coding agents)
```bash
dimagx mcp                              # Start MCP server + show config
```

---

## Connect to your agent

Add to `.claude/mcp.json` (Claude Code) or `.cursor/mcp.json` (Cursor/Windsurf):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "dimagx": {
      "command": "dimagx-mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

Your agent now has access to:

| MCP Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `get_context()` | Full project orientation — call at session start |
| `query_memory(question)` | Search across all memory layers |
| `log_prompt(text, summary, outcome)` | Capture agent work into graph |
| `add_decision(title, context, choice, reason)` | Log ADR from inside agent |
| `get_features(status?)` | List features, optionally filtered |
| `get_files(feature?, language?)` | List indexed files |

---

## PRD Ingestion

Set your Anthropic API key:
```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
```

Drop any PRD (Markdown, PDF, DOCX, TXT):
```bash
dimagx prd ingest ./docs/auth_prd.md
dimagx prd ingest ./docs/pricing_v2.pdf
```

DimagX will:
1. Extract text from the file
2. Summarize with Claude Haiku (fast + cheap)
3. Auto-create feature nodes from the PRD
4. Link PRD → features in the graph

Or drop files directly into `.dimagx/prd/` while `dimagx watch` is running — auto-ingested.

---

## Multi-PRD projects

Each PRD is a separate node. Drop as many as you have:

```
.dimagx/prd/
├── prd_auth.md
├── prd_pricing_v2.md
├── prd_online_store.pdf
└── prd_finedine.md
```

PRDs link to features. Features link to files. Files link to commits. The graph connects everything.

---

## What gets stored

| Layer | Source | Auto? |
|---|---|---|
| Files | Codebase | ✅ on init + watch |
| Git commits | Git history | ✅ on init + hook |
| Features | You / agent | Manual / MCP |
| PRDs | You drop files | ✅ watch auto-ingests |
| Prompts | Agent sessions | Via MCP `log_prompt` |
| Decisions | You / agent | `dimagx decision add` / MCP |

---

## Folder structure (per project)

```
your-project/
└── .dimagx/
    ├── config.yaml      # Project identity + stack
    ├── graph.db         # Kuzu embedded graph (gitignored)
    ├── prd/             # Drop PRDs here
    ├── features/        # Feature metadata
    └── decisions/       # ADR markdown files
```

`graph.db` is gitignored by default. `config.yaml` can be committed.

---

## Environment variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for PRD summarization |

